value.name: V1298 Tauri - Wikipedia
value.snippet: V1298 Tauri has a spectral type of K0 - K1.5 and it has a mass of about 1.1 M☉. The star appears in x-rays from ROSAT data and it does show strong lithium absorption lines, both signatures of youth and therefore it was a proposed member of Taurus-Auriga. On the other hand it does not show signs of accretion and it lacks infrared excess.
